Cristiano Ronaldo scored a 95th-minute winner as Manchester United snatched a 2-1 victory over Villarreal at Old Trafford on Wednesday. Ronaldo had barely threatened until he fired past Geronimo Rulli at the back post to ease the mounting pressure on United manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer with virtually the last kick of the game. Also Read: Messi Scores First Goal For PSG Against Man City United were staring down the barrel of another embarrassing group-stage exit from the Champions League after deservedly falling behind early in the second half to Paco Alcacer’s smart finish. Alex Telles’ stunning strike quickly levelled, but a sixth draw from open play in as many meetings between the sides was on the cards until Ronaldo’s late intervention.